                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="178.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="2.1 Angles and Trigonometric Functions Trigonometry begins with understanding angles and their measurements in degrees and radians. Using the unit circle, you’ll learn to relate angles to coordinates and explore the six main trigonometric functions: sine, cosine, tangent, cosecant, secant, and cotangent. These functions describe ratios in triangles and form the basis for modeling periodic behavior like sound or motion." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
