                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="427.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Trigonometric functions create wave-like graphs that repeat over intervals, known as periodic functions. In this section, you'll graph sine, cosine, and tangent functions, adjusting for amplitude, frequency, and phase shifts. Understanding these changes helps interpret patterns in nature and technology, such as tides, music, and oscillating circuits." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="522.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="You’ll also study trigonometric identities, formulas that hold true for all inputs. These identities allow you to simplify complex expressions and solve tricky equations. Key formulas such as the Pythagorean identity and angle addition identities are essential tools for further study and practical application in many STEM fields." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
